1
00:00:01,655 --> 00:00:05,055
[music playing]

2
00:01:37,066 --> 00:01:43,932
[gong]

3
00:01:44,032 --> 00:01:44,766
-[speaking japanese]

4
00:01:52,299 --> 00:01:57,399
-[speaking japanese]

5
00:01:57,499 --> 00:01:59,332
[gong]

6
00:01:59,432 --> 00:02:09,099
-[speaking japanese]

7
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,920
NARRATOR: The last
days of Happosai.

8
00:02:19,387 --> 00:02:20,253
-I'm serious.

9
00:02:20,353 --> 00:02:22,187
She hasn't been
wrong yet, not once.

10
00:02:22,287 --> 00:02:24,453
-But how can you be sure
it's not a coincidence?

11
00:02:24,553 --> 00:02:26,087
I mean, come on.

12
00:02:26,187 --> 00:02:29,120
The future isn't something you
can predict with tarot cards,

13
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:30,253
now is it?

14
00:02:30,353 --> 00:02:33,053
-So Miyo, can you, like,
do this for a career?

15
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,387
-[laughing] I don't see why not.

16
00:02:35,487 --> 00:02:38,487
After all, I have been
blessed with a second sight.

17
00:02:38,587 --> 00:02:40,920
Other women in my family
have been successful.

18
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:42,887
I don't see why I wouldn't be.

19
00:02:42,987 --> 00:02:46,620
Better get your cards read
now before I'm too famous.

20
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,653
So who wants to go next?

21
00:02:48,753 --> 00:02:49,687
-Let's see.

22
00:02:49,787 --> 00:02:53,087
Who else hasn't had
their future read.

23
00:02:53,187 --> 00:02:54,220
Oh, yeah, Akane!

24
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,420
Well, you haven't had
them done yet, have you?

25
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,620
-Well, no.

26
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,253
But there's nothing I
really want to know. so--

27
00:02:59,353 --> 00:02:59,920
-Oh, come on.

28
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:00,953
Don't be like that.

29
00:03:01,053 --> 00:03:02,020
I mean, what about Ranma?

30
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,020
I'm sure you'd like
to know about him.

31
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,020
-N-not really.

32
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,987
I would like to know
about the dojo, though.

33
00:03:08,087 --> 00:03:11,953
So maybe I should get my
future read after all.

34
00:03:19,087 --> 00:03:20,087
-The cards have spoken.

35
00:03:22,753 --> 00:03:26,053
Ah, yes, of course.

36
00:03:26,153 --> 00:03:28,820
Within one week's time,
you and your fiance

37
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:31,487
are destined to be married.

38
00:03:31,587 --> 00:03:32,820
-What?!

39
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,920
-Me, married?

40
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:36,320
You sure?

41
00:03:36,420 --> 00:03:37,020
No way!

42
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:37,561
No way!

43
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:38,587
It's a lie!

44
00:03:38,687 --> 00:03:39,787
There's got to be a mistake!

45
00:03:39,887 --> 00:03:41,653
You must have read them
wrong or something.

46
00:03:41,753 --> 00:03:44,020
-Ah, but the cards
never lie, you see?

47
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,587
If they see something
will happen, it'll happen.

48
00:03:46,687 --> 00:03:48,153
-Oh, my gosh, Akane.

49
00:03:48,253 --> 00:03:51,420
I had no idea you and
Ranma had gone so far.

50
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,420
-Yeah, no kidding.

51
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,487
I mean, I thought
best friends were

52
00:03:53,587 --> 00:03:55,153
supposed to tell each
other everything.

53
00:03:55,253 --> 00:03:56,787
What do you want for
a wedding present?

54
00:03:56,887 --> 00:03:57,787
-Yeah, what do you want?

55
00:03:57,887 --> 00:03:59,087
-Who's your maid of honor?

56
00:03:59,187 --> 00:04:00,553
[interposing voices]

57
00:04:00,653 --> 00:04:02,220
RANMA: Wait up, you old freak!

58
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:02,987
-What do you know.

59
00:04:03,087 --> 00:04:04,920
Here comes the bridegroom.

60
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:06,220
-Return that underwear!

61
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,953
I told you the
school's off limits.

62
00:04:08,053 --> 00:04:10,487
-I see you've got some
underwear here yourself, my boy.

63
00:04:10,587 --> 00:04:11,453
Who would have known?

64
00:04:11,553 --> 00:04:12,520
Ha-ha.

65
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:13,920
RANMA: That's cause
I took it from you.

66
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:16,887
HAPPOSAI: [laughing]

67
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,820
[glass breaking]

68
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,787
-Did I just see an old man?

69
00:04:23,887 --> 00:04:27,753
[gasps] The tower!

70
00:04:27,853 --> 00:04:30,720
[gasps]

71
00:04:40,753 --> 00:04:42,287
-Slippery little freak.

72
00:04:42,387 --> 00:04:44,253
I'll take care of him
once we get home, though.

73
00:04:44,353 --> 00:04:45,553
Just you wait.

74
00:04:45,653 --> 00:04:48,353
You know, for such an old
guy, he ain't half bad.

75
00:04:48,453 --> 00:04:50,353
He ought to last at
least another 100 years.

76
00:04:50,453 --> 00:04:51,853
-Uh, Ranma?

77
00:04:51,953 --> 00:04:52,953
-Yeah?

78
00:04:53,053 --> 00:04:54,987
-Do you believe in destiny?

79
00:04:55,087 --> 00:04:55,753
-Destiny?

80
00:04:55,853 --> 00:04:57,120
Oh, I get it.

81
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:59,420
Everyone's talking about that
whacked-out chick at school.

82
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,253
I'll bet you had
your cards read, huh?

83
00:05:01,353 --> 00:05:02,387
Nah.

84
00:05:02,487 --> 00:05:04,420
You make your own fate,
as far as I'm concerned.

85
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,353
So, uh, why do you ask?

86
00:05:06,453 --> 00:05:08,520
Is there something about
me in your future, or what?

87
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:11,887
-Uh, none of your beeswax.

88
00:05:11,987 --> 00:05:13,353
You don't believe in it, anyway.

89
00:05:13,453 --> 00:05:13,894
RANMA: Ha!

90
00:05:13,953 --> 00:05:15,220
I knew it!

91
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,253
AKANE: She did say something
else that worries me, though.

92
00:05:17,353 --> 00:05:19,953
She said it right after you and
Happosai left the classroom.

93
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:21,353
MIYO (VOICEOVER):
That old man who

94
00:05:21,453 --> 00:05:23,920
just ran though has
been marked by fate.

95
00:05:24,020 --> 00:05:25,887
I fer the misfortune
of a coming illness

96
00:05:25,987 --> 00:05:28,120
may somehow involve you, Akane.

97
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:30,853
Please be careful.

98
00:05:30,953 --> 00:05:31,720
-Huh!

99
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:34,053
-Jeez, don't scare me like that.

100
00:05:34,153 --> 00:05:35,287
-L-look!

101
00:05:35,387 --> 00:05:35,828
AKANE: Huh?

102
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:39,953
RANMA: It's the
freak's collection.

103
00:05:40,053 --> 00:05:43,153
AKANE: It's leading
up to our house.

104
00:05:43,253 --> 00:05:44,120
RANMA: Yo, pops!

105
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:45,053
AKANE: Dad?

106
00:05:45,153 --> 00:05:46,153
RANMA: Pops, what is it?

107
00:05:46,253 --> 00:05:47,520
SOUN: Master, what's wrong?

108
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:48,620
GENMA: What is it, Master?

109
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,187
-Huh?

110
00:05:49,287 --> 00:05:49,887
GENMA: Tell us!

111
00:05:49,987 --> 00:05:50,453
RANMA: Gramps?

112
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:53,761
Gramps!

113
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,487
-Hmm?

114
00:05:55,587 --> 00:05:57,087
What is it, Ranma?

115
00:05:57,187 --> 00:06:00,053
-Well, you left your
collection laying all over.

116
00:06:00,153 --> 00:06:00,787
-Keep it.

117
00:06:00,887 --> 00:06:02,120
It's all yours.

118
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:03,220
-What?

119
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,287
But-- but you worked
really hard to build it.

120
00:06:05,387 --> 00:06:07,287
You can't just throw it away!

121
00:06:07,387 --> 00:06:08,787
-Sure I can.

122
00:06:13,287 --> 00:06:14,187
-Here, Master.

123
00:06:14,287 --> 00:06:15,920
We've brought you
something to eat.

124
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:19,587
-We can't have you wasting
away in your room now, can we?

125
00:06:19,687 --> 00:06:20,920
It's your favorite snack.

126
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:21,520
-Take it away.

127
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:22,453
I don't want it.

128
00:06:22,553 --> 00:06:25,220
All I want now is
to go to sleep.

129
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,153
Shut the door on your way out.

130
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:31,020
SOUN: [sighs] He's been
like that since he got home.

131
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:35,320
GENMA: Since when does
the master turn down food?

132
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:37,953
AKANE: He's definitely
acting strange.

133
00:06:38,053 --> 00:06:39,920
The poor dear must be ill.

134
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:43,620
GIRL: The old lech starts acting
human and we call him sick?

135
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,487
RANMA: Hey, so long as
he's not bothering us,

136
00:06:45,587 --> 00:06:48,187
he can stay in there
all day for all I care.

137
00:06:48,287 --> 00:06:50,020
-Speaking of which, boy!

138
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:52,387
-Hey, that tea's cold, pop!

139
00:06:52,487 --> 00:06:53,953
What are you doing?

140
00:06:54,053 --> 00:06:54,620
Let me go.

141
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,353
-Master, catch!

142
00:06:57,453 --> 00:06:59,220
-That you, Ranma?

143
00:06:59,320 --> 00:06:59,820
Cover up.

144
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:00,920
You'll catch cold.

145
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,887
It is a far, far
better rest that I

146
00:07:07,987 --> 00:07:10,687
go to than I have ever known.

147
00:07:10,787 --> 00:07:12,020
-Master, don't go!

148
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,453
-Master, are you
saying you're leaving?

149
00:07:14,553 --> 00:07:15,420
HAPPOSAI: I must.

150
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,987
-Master, you mustn't
talk like this.

151
00:07:17,087 --> 00:07:18,787
Why, you're still in
the prime of life.

152
00:07:18,887 --> 00:07:20,353
There's no reason
to believe you won't

153
00:07:20,453 --> 00:07:22,587
be with us for another
hundred years at least.

154
00:07:22,687 --> 00:07:23,420
SOUN: Saotome, look.

155
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:23,953
-What?

156
00:07:24,053 --> 00:07:24,587
What is it?

157
00:07:24,687 --> 00:07:26,720
What do you want?

158
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:27,953
-Look.

159
00:07:28,053 --> 00:07:30,687
-Th-- th-- th-- that's snow
in the middle of summer.

160
00:07:30,787 --> 00:07:33,287
SOUN: It's an evil omen.

161
00:07:33,387 --> 00:07:36,753
[cawing]

162
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,787
-Soun, Genma.

163
00:07:41,887 --> 00:07:42,453
-Go on.

164
00:07:42,553 --> 00:07:43,487
We're listening.

165
00:07:43,587 --> 00:07:45,887
-I'm not long for this world.

166
00:07:45,987 --> 00:07:48,487
When that time comes,
you'll know what to do.

167
00:07:48,587 --> 00:07:50,720
It's all written
down in my will.

168
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:52,120
SOUND AND GENMA: Master!

169
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:54,487
No!

170
00:07:54,587 --> 00:07:56,853
HAPPOSAI: [gasping for air]

171
00:07:56,953 --> 00:08:00,620
-If anything ever happened to
him, I don't know what I'd do.

172
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,587
-However, there's
a good possibility

173
00:08:02,687 --> 00:08:05,687
that this time the
master may not recover.

174
00:08:05,787 --> 00:08:06,953
-True.

175
00:08:07,053 --> 00:08:09,487
Snow in the middle of summer,
ravens on the rooftop--

176
00:08:09,587 --> 00:08:11,787
all signs are
pointing to the worst.

177
00:08:11,887 --> 00:08:14,120
-Can the Anything Goes
School of Martial Arts

178
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:15,920
survive the loss
of the master who

179
00:08:16,020 --> 00:08:18,553
founded its techniques
in the first place?

180
00:08:18,653 --> 00:08:19,587
Is this the end?

181
00:08:19,687 --> 00:08:20,387
-No!

182
00:08:20,487 --> 00:08:21,853
Not so long as we're alive!

183
00:08:21,953 --> 00:08:24,053
The Anything Goes School is
something for which we've

184
00:08:24,153 --> 00:08:25,853
shed blood, sweat, and tears.

185
00:08:25,953 --> 00:08:27,620
Are you ready to
throw it all away?

186
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,153
We have to do
something, whatever

187
00:08:29,253 --> 00:08:31,920
it takes to make
sure it goes on.

188
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:35,453
-For our school, no
sacrifice can be too great.

189
00:08:35,553 --> 00:08:37,120
-Whatever it takes, Tendo.

190
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:39,353
That's what we've got to do.

191
00:08:39,453 --> 00:08:41,253
SOUND AND GENMA: Hmm!

192
00:08:41,353 --> 00:08:45,087
[wind howling]

193
00:08:45,187 --> 00:08:47,287
-[gasps] That has to be it.

194
00:08:47,387 --> 00:08:49,253
Tarot cards, crystal
ball, Ouija board.

195
00:08:49,353 --> 00:08:52,087
No matter what fortune-telling
method I use to try and predict

196
00:08:52,187 --> 00:08:54,920
the future, the result
always comes out the same.

197
00:08:55,020 --> 00:08:58,420
Something awful is about to
happen at the Tendo residence.

198
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,520
And it's probably
already started.

199
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:03,287
It's the old man,
just as I've foreseen.

200
00:09:03,387 --> 00:09:05,220
He's destined to bring disaster.

201
00:09:08,087 --> 00:09:11,220
-I think Pop and your dad were
up with the old man all night.

202
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,087
-Too bad it took something
like this for them

203
00:09:13,187 --> 00:09:15,520
to finally be nice
to him, huh, Ranma?

204
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:16,953
-Yeah, I guess you're right.

205
00:09:17,053 --> 00:09:18,753
-He is their master, after all.

206
00:09:18,853 --> 00:09:20,753
It's only natural
that they're worried.

207
00:09:20,853 --> 00:09:22,487
-Something was wrong
with him, though.

208
00:09:22,587 --> 00:09:23,687
That's for sure.

209
00:09:23,787 --> 00:09:25,887
I don't think we should
be too worried about him.

210
00:09:25,987 --> 00:09:28,420
He'll be back to his
obnoxious self in no time.

211
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,420
-I hope you're right.

212
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,253
RANMA: Huh?

213
00:09:30,353 --> 00:09:31,087
AKANE: Huh?

214
00:09:31,187 --> 00:09:32,487
RANMA: What the heck is that?

215
00:09:32,587 --> 00:09:35,387
Gee, what's the celebration for?

216
00:09:35,487 --> 00:09:37,520
AKANE: It's in here too.

217
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:38,920
Nabiki, what's--

218
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:41,587
-Your future is about to
be decided in the dojo.

219
00:09:41,687 --> 00:09:46,120
So you lovebirds had best
hurry up and get over there.

220
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:46,653
RANMA: OK.

221
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:47,287
We're here.

222
00:09:47,387 --> 00:09:48,653
What do you want?

223
00:09:48,753 --> 00:09:51,587
-I'm sure you both are aware
that the master's condition has

224
00:09:51,687 --> 00:09:53,720
only gotten worse,
and that the master

225
00:09:53,820 --> 00:09:57,787
himself seems to have somehow
lost the will to live.

226
00:09:57,887 --> 00:10:00,153
Ranma, while the master
is still alive to see it,

227
00:10:00,253 --> 00:10:03,887
I want you and Akane to wed,
to carry on the Anything Goes

228
00:10:03,987 --> 00:10:04,820
School.

229
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:05,487
-What?!

230
00:10:05,587 --> 00:10:06,653
-Marriage?

231
00:10:06,753 --> 00:10:08,987
-Ranma, my boy,
it is your destiny

232
00:10:09,087 --> 00:10:11,287
to sire enough children
to carry on the Anything

233
00:10:11,387 --> 00:10:13,820
Goes School for
generations to come.

234
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,820
-Akane, it may be
asking a lot of you.

235
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,753
But you've known for a long
time now that it's your destiny

236
00:10:18,853 --> 00:10:20,687
to be a good wife to Ranma.

237
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:24,220
-The ceremony will be held five
days from now in this dojo.

238
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,620
-As your future father-in-law,
son, I thank you.

239
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,620
-Thank you, Akane.

240
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:30,253
-Five days from now?

241
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:35,587
-I know it's an emergency.

242
00:10:35,687 --> 00:10:37,020
But they're still
in high school.

243
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,687
Isn't it too soon?

244
00:10:38,787 --> 00:10:40,720
-Seeing as it's not
a real marriage,

245
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:43,120
and there's no sense in
spending more than we have to,

246
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:47,753
how would you feel about
cold cuts and a no-host bar?

247
00:10:47,853 --> 00:10:49,220
[thunder]

248
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,087
RANMA (VOICEOVER):
Akane, please be patient.

249
00:10:51,187 --> 00:10:54,220
I'll be showering you with
souvenirs before you know it.

250
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:57,620
The strange feeling in the
air worries me, though.

251
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,520
Shouldn't it be the
middle of summer?

252
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:02,953
I've got a bad
feeling about this.

253
00:11:03,053 --> 00:11:03,953
[rain]

254
00:11:04,053 --> 00:11:04,953
RANMA: Oh, great.

255
00:11:05,053 --> 00:11:05,753
This is all I need!

256
00:11:30,316 --> 00:11:33,216
[rain]

257
00:11:39,085 --> 00:11:40,752
AKANE (VOICEOVER): I
can hardly believe it.

258
00:11:40,852 --> 00:11:44,118
But if Master Happosai
doesn't get better soon,

259
00:11:44,218 --> 00:11:48,352
five days from now Ranma
and I will be married!

260
00:11:48,452 --> 00:11:50,152
-Stop worrying, Akane.

261
00:11:50,252 --> 00:11:53,085
I'm telling you, this marriage
ain't never gonna happen.

262
00:11:53,185 --> 00:11:55,918
It's gonna take a lot more than
this to stop the old freak.

263
00:11:56,018 --> 00:11:59,052
I'll bet you money it's just
an act to try and scare us.

264
00:11:59,152 --> 00:12:00,185
-You really think so?

265
00:12:00,285 --> 00:12:00,885
[window rattling]

266
00:12:00,985 --> 00:12:03,285
-Who's there?

267
00:12:03,385 --> 00:12:04,252
[pig squealing]

268
00:12:04,352 --> 00:12:07,118
-If it isn't P-Chan!

269
00:12:07,218 --> 00:12:08,085
Ah!

270
00:12:08,185 --> 00:12:09,852
[laughing] Look at you.

271
00:12:09,952 --> 00:12:10,618
You're soaking wet.

272
00:12:10,718 --> 00:12:12,585
You poor baby.

273
00:12:12,685 --> 00:12:14,252
You must be so cold.

274
00:12:14,352 --> 00:12:15,752
Let Mommy warm
you up in her bed.

275
00:12:20,885 --> 00:12:21,852
